OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FPay rises at fastest pace  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ffor over 20 years          
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Wages have grown at the fastest rate in
OL,6, over 20 years, but are still failing to
OL,7, keep up with rising prices.            
OL,9,FRegular pay, which excludes bonuses,   
OL,10,Frose at an annual pace of 6.4% between 
OL,11,FSeptember and November, official       
OL,12,Ffigures show.                          
OL,14,FIt marks the fastest growth since 2001,
OL,15,Fexcluding the pandemic, when people got
OL,16,Fbig rises after returning to work from 
OL,17,Ffurlough.                              
OL,19,FHowever, when adjusted for rising      
OL,20,Fprices, wages fell by 2.6%.            
